==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: follow-on
<hw>follow-on</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an immediate second innings forced
on a cricket team scoring a prescribed number of runs fewer than its
opponents in the first innings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>follow-on</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: follow-on
<hw>follow-on</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Following as a logical consequence
or next step in a process; -- used mostly of voluntary
actions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>follow-through</ent>⟦br⟧
